If you have a column that specifies the ordering.  One uses `lag()` and a cumulative sum:

    select t.*,
           sum(case when prev_column is null or prev_column &lt;&gt; column
                    then 1 else 0
               end) over (order by ?)
    from (select t.*, lag(column) over (order by ?) as prev_column
          from t
         ) t;

`?` is for the ordering column.

